style=3D"mso-tab-count: 1">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>The notion of =
a=20
full-REA model or an epistemologically adequate schema is explained in =
great=20
detail by Geerts and McCarthy (2000b).Basically, it means that no =
stock-flow or=20
duality relationships may be compromised in an REA implementation.In =
other=20
words, the full REA template must always be instantiated; to do =
otherwise=20
disables the possibilities for pattern-matched=20
inference.</P></DIV></DIV></BODY></HTML>

